          <msContents>
            <summary>Collection of hymns, mantras, and praises to the Sun god (Āditya also called Sūrya) used for private or public recitation, meditation, and prayer. presented as a conversation between the legendary prince Arjuna and the Hindu deity Kṛṣṇa. Last part of colophon (starting: śrīādityāyanamaḥ) written in a different scribal hand.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Ādityahṛdayastotra</title>
              <title type="vernacular">आदित्यहृदयस्तोत्र</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrībhaviṣyottarapurāṇe śrīkṛṣṇārjunasaṃvāde ādityahṛdayastotraṃ saṃpūrṇaṃ // subham astu // idaṃ pustakaṃ paropakārārthaṃ // śrīādityāyanamaḥ // rāmaḥ // pustakam etad dharmādhikārinārāyaṇasya // bhānave namaḥ // cha // cha // (f. 12v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
